## Revolutionary Impact Statement

This open-source project democratizes microplastic detection technology,
reducing costs from ₹50,00,000 to ₹4,000 - a 100x improvement that makes
environmental monitoring accessible to communities worldwide.

## Attribution

If you use this software in academic research, commercial applications, or
derivative works, please cite:

"ESP32-CAM Microplastic Detection System - A Revolutionary Cost-Effective
Solution for Environmental Monitoring. AquaGuard Innovators, SIH 2025."

## Community Contribution

This project is released under MIT License to encourage:
- Educational use in schools and universities
- Research applications in environmental science
- Commercial deployment for water quality monitoring  
- Community development and enhancement
- Global environmental protection efforts

The revolutionary ₹4,000 cost point enables deployment in:
- Rural communities
- Developing regions
- Educational institutions
- Research laboratories
- Government monitoring networks
- NGO environmental programs

## Support Environmental Protection

By making this technology freely available, we aim to accelerate the global
response to microplastic pollution and democratize access to advanced
environmental monitoring tools.

Together, we can make clean water monitoring affordable for everyone.